<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Teal</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-08-14 18:34:58</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Haste comes in 4 forms...(at least on weapons)<BR>
<BR>
1) Permanent Item Based (like on a FBSS)<BR>
2) Process Effect Item Based (Proc: Executioner's Axe)<BR>
3) Spell Based (Haste Spells: Alacrity, Celerity, Bard Songs)<BR>
4) Inherent (Monks level 25+ have natural haste)<BR>
<BR>
Since this item has effect: haste, it is one of the first two types of haste. Also, since there is no spell in the game (save the effect itself) called "Haste" it is not the third. It is not the 4th obviously.<BR>
<BR>
It is highly unlikely that the item is permanent haste but truthfully there's only one way to find out and that's to weild the weapon. If ever so often you see something like:<BR>
"Your will is not sufficient to command this weapon" or "You feel faster" then the haste is a proc. Otherwise it's perm.<BR>
<BR>
</font></td></tr></table>
